review_blob: Dark yellow color, almost orange.  Whitish head.  Medium body, somewhat dry and mouth cleaning.  Sweet and a hint of fruit light bitterness.  Very carbonated.  Mild hops.  Good.
This was a great stout.  Very reminiscent of my favorite coffee.  Sweet chocolate flavor as well.  Good that I dont drink this very often might get too fat.
Very good.  Slightly bitter, roasty with huge notes of caramel.  Could drink this all year long.  Very good. Bravo.
Dark body, sweet aroma.  Notes of chocolate and coffee,  Hints of molasses and caramel.  Very good porter indeed.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Tast like an alcoholic lemonade.  Do not drink late at night as you will taste it all night.  not my favorite.
Nice cloudy golden color, bready and strong banana esters.  Very good job from Flying Dog.
Nice amber color, Citrus, and earth.  Very pronounced hop character but not too much.  Nice beer.
Light yellow, Thin head.  Yeasty smell sweet with mild hops.  Nice yet forgettable.  Maybe a good session beer.
Thin yellow and some what gross.  Rice and fillers also skunky.  I am sorry I ever tried this..
Dark dark brown.  Very hoppy.  Very strong and very intense.  If you have not had this style before be prepared.  This beer is Very intense.
Amber colored with a soft white head.  Malty with hints of caramel, and just a hint of spicyness.  Dry and alittle thin.  Alittle grassiness as well.
Aroma is very thin and grainy.  Smells of corn...  Almost reminds me of watered down budwieser.
Very hoppy, not like an IPA but still.  Crisp, dry and smooth.  Lots of things going on here.  Citrus and floral, as well as spicy.  Nice.
Copper body with white head. Light lacing. Noticable hope flavor, Perhaps cascade?  Slightly sweet and fruity, went down very nicely.  Pairs well with a hot day like today.
Golden pink pour, very little head.  Light sediment.  Fruity aroma and flavor.  Very easy to drink and really refreshing after a hot day at the Iowa state fair.  Liked it.
Black and clingy.  Aroma is very strong, oak, tobacco, wine, chocolate and dark coffee, thick and chewy feeling in the mouth.  Very strong. warms you all the way down.  Worth Trying.
Dark red, very tart.  Almost sour.  Great with dessert.  Sour and intense.  Almost like a cherry soda only more intense.
Creamy whipped head, malty, strangely similar to boddingtons pub ale.  Very good session ale.  Love it.

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: Thin tart and sparkly.  Very smooth goes down way to fast.  Can easliy drink a sixer before you know it.  Fast drunk...
Tart and very much like a caramel apple.  Very good, and strangely it caused a really fast drunk.  Hmm...
Creamy head, light, fruity apricot aroma. Mouth is fruity. Its silky with light bitterness. Palate, is astringent.
Honey, toasty,and doughy.  Brown Slight hop, resinous.  Sweet, very drinkable.
Golden with moderate white head.  Grain and sour malt.  Slight hop, hints of fruit, and minerals.  Slight honey. Good.
Clear golden color, moderate head with minor lacing.  Aroma of Saaz and Grass,  Very drinkable and smooth, especialy if you are a fan of Saaz hops.  I loved it.
Very thin and yellow brew.  Mine was slightly skunky.  Slightly industrial smell in the glass.  Not one I liked
Golden color, alittle hop, some sweetness tasted like a strange version of bud or something.
This was a pale straw colored brew that was sweet and smooth.  Alittle cloudy as well went down well enough but not my favorite
Hay color and flavor, bitter and thin.  Not bad for being from india.  Very bitter and disappointing
This was a very good porter, however very similar to the milk stout.  Has a darker chocolate flavor though.
Dark malty stout sweet sour taste, Very smooth and delicious.  Mouth coating feel, I think I could drink this all day long. Awesome brew.

Pour was a light amber with a small fizzy white head.  Nose of caramel and spruce.  Taste was heavy of caramel, toffee, brown sugar, and light spruce.  Wonderful flavor, and very smooth.   This has the best caramel flavor ever.

This beer poured a light amber, topped by a frothy head of average size, white in color, with a clear body.  After a few moments the head mostly diminished, leaving fair lace.  Nose was of light citrus, a hint of soap, and grain.  Taste of brown sugar, light alcohol, and a hint of sugar cookies.  Flavor was moderatly sweet, with a light bitter finish.  Creamy texture, light to medium body, and flat in the mouth.  As far as this style goes, I am very pleased with this beer.

Pour was a hazy dark mauve with average head, awesome lace.  Nose of raspberrys.  Flavor was heavy sweet with some acidicness, tasted of raspberrys, hops, wine, and oak.  Palate was creamy, medium body, with a lively alcoholic feel.  Low points on the aroma as there doesnt seem to be alot going on.  Otherwise this is an excellent fruit beer.  I can say that this is one to sip and enjoy.  Bravo.

Appearance was average rocky off white head, some lace.  Dark amber body.  Nose of perfume and pine.  Cask wood.  Taste of molassess, raisins, light honey, alcohol, and bourbon.  Bittersweet.  Very heavy alcoholic feel.  Like sipping Jack Daniels.  Overall a decent winter warmer.

1Q 14.5oz bottle.  Intial pour reveals an amber brew with a sparkling body and a huge creamy off white head.  Good lacing.  Nose of heavy malt, grass, pineapple, and alcohol.  Tasting reveals a heavy sticky sweet beer with a full body and creamy texture, notes of caramel, toffee, honey, and rice.  Slightly alcoholic feel.  Very excellent taste, I must say I am impressed with this.  To bad that all Bud couldnt be this good.  This is truly a king of beers.

Drank this after Moosehead.  Much Better.  Very smooth and refreshing.  Nose of bread or cookies, and caramel.  Taste of brown sugar.  No head, artificial.  Good tasting, but gets low points for being to simple.

This beer is Heineken by a different name.  Aroma consist of grain, perfume, grass, citrus, and saaz.  Soap, oak, corn, and overpowering solvent.  Body was light amber.  Creamy off white head.  Excellent lacing.  Bitter sweet.  Huge metallic copper taste upfront followed by sweet maltiness.  Good session if you like Heineken.  Overall not impressive.

Brew poured a dark brown  with a fizzy brown head.  Fair Lace.  Nose of chocolate, sweat, toffee, and brown sugar.  Taste of caramel, pine and saw dust.  Watery and metallic.  Nice session easy to drink but lacks substance.

Beautiful golden pour with average white creamy head.  Excellent lacing.  Bottle conditioned.  Aroma of bread, straw and cereal, some cookie, perfume and citrus.  Hint of corn.  Nice flavor.  Light to medium body somewhat oily and soft.  Enjoyable with lemon or orange.  An excellent example of its style.

Brewed by FBG Toronto Canada, pours a light amber with average head and some lacing.  Nose was of sulfur.  Taste was grainy, some resin, light dough and spicy like a corona with bread.  Overall a very poor example of Ausie beer.  However what can you expect of an Ausie beer made in Canada?

Nice deep golden color.  Nose of cookies and grain.  Light citrus.  Moderate dough and soap.  Very light hints of banana and honey.  Not bad but not good.  Decent wheat beer but I think Boulevard does it better.
Watery and somewhat flavorless.  Not sure what I expected.  I have had this before and enjoyed but this time was horrible.
Very nice taste.  Goes down smooth.  Nice sweet flavor.  Could drink this all the time.  I think this would be great to fill in for or replace any standard session.  Thank you Germany.

Light hints of grain and caramel, chocolate, coffee, citrus, dough, and nutty.  Average creamy off white creamy head with good lacing.  Dark brown color.  Sweet up front bitter behind.  Meduim body, creamy texture light alcoholic feel.  Good stuff.
beer_name: Rock Bottom Des Moines Lumpy Dog Brown

review_blob: Pour reveals a light amber colored brew with average head and good lacing.  Nose reveals light caramel, flowers, citrus, alcohol, and apricots.  Light sweetness in the mouth moderately bitter.  Average duration.  Light to meduim body.
beer_name: Rock Bottom Des Moines White Tail Pale Ale

beer_brewer_name: CraftWorks Restaurants & Breweries -Rock Bottom Corporate Office
review_blob: Watery, wet grain, grassy. Light alcoholic flavor.  Light yellow with an average head.  Good lacing.  Bannana esters.
beer_name: Rock Bottom Lumpy Dog Light Lager

review_blob: Pour was medium red with an off white avarage head and good lacing.  Aroma of Caramel milk chocolate and slight mild coffee.  Light notes of herbs, and hints of dough.  Strong hints of raisins.  Moderately sweet with a meduim body, creamy texture, and light alcoholic feel.
beer_name: Rock Bottom Des Moines Mud in Your Eye Red

review_blob: UPDATED: JAN 1, 2007

Beautiful hasy medium amber body.  Average head with good lacing.  Aroma was very hoppy, herbs, grapefruit and some light pine.  Flavors of walnuts, caramel, toffee, and light grain.  Bittersweet up front, sweet finish.  Medium body, dry, and slightly metallic finish.  This was a very tasty IPA.  Flying Dog does it better, but this is one of my favorites.  I will be getting more of this.

Body was a medium amber with an off white average creamy head.  Fair lacing.  Nose was of cookies, caramel and mild coffee.  Notes of toffee.  Light hop that reminds me of Saaz.  Whispers of skunk.  Moderately sweet with a hint of something bitter and skunky on the swallow.  Light to medium body.  Mouth was watery.  Not bad.  Hard to distinguish between this and Samuel Adams octoberfest.  Nice session.
